<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id9088f766-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s5306"><num value="5306">§ 5306.</num><heading> Definitions</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">As used in this subchapter:</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I79" class="indent3 firstIndent-2" id="id9088f767-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s5306/1"><num value="1" class="bold">(1)</num><heading class="bold"> Secretary</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1">The term “Secretary” means the Secretary of the Treasury.</p>
</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I79" class="indent3 firstIndent-2" id="id9088f768-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s5306/2"><num value="2" class="bold">(2)</num><heading class="bold"> Board</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1">The term “Board” means the Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System.</p>
</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id9088f769-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">(<ref href="/us/pl/100/418/tIII/s3006">Pub. L. 100–418, title III, § 3006</ref>, <date date="1988-08-23">Aug. 23, 1988</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/102/1375">102 Stat. 1375</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id9088f76a-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id9088f76b-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I75" topic="referencesInText" id="id9088f76c-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">
<heading class="centered smallCaps">References in Text</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">This subchapter, referred to in text, was in the original “this subtitle”, meaning subtitle A (§§ 3001–3006) of title III of <ref href="/us/pl/100/418">Pub. L. 100–418</ref>, <date date="1988-08-23">Aug. 23, 1988</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/102/1372">102 Stat. 1372</ref>, which is classified principally to this subchapter. For complete classification of subtitle A to the Code, see Tables.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
